		<pb n="1"/>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Synagogue Chambers</placeName></p>
          <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Philad.</placeName> <date>Shebat 4<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 5611</date></p>
          <p rend="align(right)"><date>January 7<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1851</date></p>
			<p>Dear Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Your Letter of <date>8<hi rend="sup">th</hi> Nov</date> addressed to the<lb/> wardens of our congregation was received and sub&#61;<lb/>mitted to the Parnass and Adjunta who compose the<lb/> Board of Managers&#44; it should have met with<lb/> an earlier answer but for a pressure of business<lb/> engagements&#44; and in Conformity with your request<lb/> I proceed to give you as nearly as possible the information<lb/> requested&#44;&#8212;The office of Hazan is vacant&#44; and the<lb/> congregation have agreed to go into an election for one<lb/> on the <date>13<hi rend="sup">th</hi> April</date>&#44; The term of service was to have been<lb/> originally ten years but owing to particular &#38; peculiar cir<lb/>&#61;cumstances not necessary to be here narrated I am<lb/> of the opinion that no new incumbent will be engaged<lb/> at the outset for more than Three years and that the<lb/> ten years term will be rescinded. The salary to a<lb/> single man will be &#36;1300&#44; to a married man seventeen<lb/> hundred Dollars &#40;&#36;1700&#41; per annum. The Hazan will<lb/> be expected to say all the usual prayers of <date>sabbath</date><lb/> eve&#44; morning&#44; afternoon &#38; conclusion service&#44; and on<lb/> holy&#45;days &#38; festivals with no other aid except in the<lb/> Haphtara &#38; on <date>Kippur day</date> &#44; it is not by law any part<lb/> of his duty to deliver English discourses but as it has<lb/> been for many years the custom to do so&#44; an occa<lb/>&#61;sional address or moral lecture in English will be<lb/> expected. The Hazan is to perform all marriage and<lb/> funeral services in the congregation and to attend<lb/> the seven days mourning service&#44; he will be per&#61;<lb/>&#61;mitted to keep school and indeed his ability to teach</p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p>the Hebrew will be a great desideratum&#44; but the congregation<lb/> will not be expected to do more than they bargain for and<lb/> it will depend on the popularity and abilities of the<lb/> successful candidate to make more by &#8220;Matanots&#8221; or by<lb/> teaching our youth. &#40;he is also entitled to all marriage<lb/> fees&#41; You remark in your letter &#8220;Should you<lb/> &#8220;gentlemen decide upon judging of my capability personally<lb/> &#8220;I should in all likelihood bring with me such certificates<lb/> &#8220;as to meet with your entire confidence&#44; in that case<lb/> &#8220;I should much like to receive a minute account of the<lb/> &#8220;duties attached to the Hazanship before I undertake so<lb/> &#8220;expensive a voyage&#8221;</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">I have already given you an outline<lb/> of the duties of the office but the Board can take no<lb/> action or give any advice as to whether you should come<lb/> out or not&#44; they are acting in this instance simply as<lb/> the <hi rend="underline">mouth piece</hi> of the Congregation in announcing the exis<lb/>&#61;ting vacancy&#44; the forthcoming election &#38; in corresponding<lb/> with parties interested&#44; but the election is made by<lb/> the members of the congregation at a general meeting<lb/> and not by the Board&#44; it would no doubt be very<lb/> agreeable to be able to see and hear the candidates &#38;<lb/> judge personally of their qualifications&#44; but as no provision<lb/> has been made to pay the <sic>travelling</sic> expenses of such<lb/> as wished to come on trial it must be left to the<lb/> <sic>judgement</sic> or inclination of the parties themselves whether<lb/> to come or not&#44; Under all circumstances however<lb/> it will be very important to have from the best<lb/> sources the most ample testimonials of capacity and<lb/> standing.&#160;&#160;I am dear Sir</p>
          <p rend="indent(8)">yours Very Respy</p>
          <p rend="indent(9)"><persName role="author">A&#58; Hart</persName>&#44; Parnass K.K.M.S.</p>
			<p>To <persName>Mr S. Morais</persName></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>10 Bevis Marks</placeName></p>
          <p rend="indent(2)"><placeName>London</placeName></p>
          
        </body>
